## Frequently Asked Questions

### How do I move the player?
Use the Siri Remote directional pad (or swipe gestures) to move the player up, down, left, or right. Push boxes onto the target locations to complete each level.

### How is my progress saved?
Your game progress is saved automatically on your device using SwiftData. If you are signed in to iCloud, your progress syncs across all your Apple devices.

### I lost my progress. How can I recover it?
Make sure you are signed in to the same iCloud account on your device. Your progress should sync automatically. If the issue persists, try restarting the app or your device.

### How do in-app purchases work?
Solution credits can be purchased through the app. All transactions are processed securely by Apple via StoreKit. We do not collect or store any payment information.

### How do leaderboards and achievements work?
PushBox uses Apple Game Center for leaderboards, achievements, and challenges. Make sure Game Center is enabled in your device settings to participate.

### The app is crashing or not working correctly. What should I do?
1. Make sure you have the latest version of the app installed.
2. Restart the app.
3. Restart your device.
4. If the issue persists, please contact us via email with a description of the problem.

